The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Allodium for Queens Cup 
 BY STAR RACER  Bharath Calcutta: Allodium, Another Time and Calorescence are the chief contenders for the prestigious 2,800m Queen Elizabeth II Cup at the RCTC race ground on Saturday. However, terms of the race seems grossly in favour of the Bharath Singh-trained seven-year-old Allodium who, despite his advancing age, may gallop to victory in the hands of C. Alford. The lowly weighted Another Time, the winner of the Oaks, and the in-form Calorescence are capable of extending the Twist And Turn-Dangerous Romance gelding.Race card and selections1. Predator Handicap 1,100m (Cl V; Rt. 18 amp; below) 12.05 pm: Gul 60 P. Alford 2; Heavens Blessing 60 Maseyk 5; April Ace 58.5 Amil 1; Accredit 57.5 Gajender 3; Bold Apparel 54.5 Merchant 4.1. Bold Apparel (5) 2. Heavens Blessing (2) 3. Gul (1)2. Advisor Handicap 1,400m (Cl III; Rt. 44-72) 12.35 pm: My Opinion 60 A. P. Singh 6; Alminstar 56 Gurang 4; Kargil Soldier 55.5 P. Alford 3; Lucifer 54 Upadhya 8; Rescue Act 54 Nicholls 2; Mr. Bombshell 53 R. Marshall 7; Bay Dragon 52 Kader 1; Amicable 50.5 C. Alford 5.1. Amicable (8) 2. Rescue Act (5) 3. Mr. Bombshell (6)3. Leprechaun Plate 1,100m (Terms, 3-y-o only) 1.10 pm: Davaro 55 Dalpat 4; Forest Ridge 55 Amil 6; Great Ambition 55 Kader 3; Great View 55 Yadav 2; Hoagy 55 Rutherford 8; Starry Man 55 R. Marshall 5; The Storm Rider 55 Brij S. 10; Welsh Emperor 55 Upadhya 7; Amber Song 53.5 Merchant 9; Rock Music 53.5 C. Alford 11; Ruby Star 53.5 E. Smith 1.1. Rock Music (10) 2. Starry Man (6) 3. Amber Song (9)4. Ardiles Handicap 1,100m (Cl III; 5-y-o amp; over Rt. 44-72) 1.50 pm: Crimson Rage 61 Shanker 8; Software 59.5 Gowli 6; Flossy 58.5 E. Smith 4; Sky Command 57 Gajender 3; Starina 57 Rutherford 1; Sadaf 56.5 R. Marshall 9; Gallant Romeo 55.5 Merchant 5; Abridge 52.5 Rabani 7; Meadow Royale 52 Kujur 2.1. Crimson Rage (1) 2. Abridge (8) 3. Flossy (3) 5. Queen Elizabeth II Cup 2,800m (Terms, 4-y-o amp; over) 2.25 pm: Calorescence 60 Shanker 2; Network 56.5 (Not declared to Sta